# Application Rules

## Project Overview

- This is a Next.js application using Supabase for backend services
- Deployed on Vercel
- Using TypeScript for type safety
- Using Tailwind CSS for styling

## Architecture

- Follow a feature-based architecture
- Organize code by domain/feature rather than technical concerns
- Keep business logic separate from UI components
- Use server components for data fetching and processing
- Use client components only when necessary

## State Management

- Use React's built-in state management where possible
- Use context for global state that spans multiple components
- Consider using Zustand for more complex state management
- Avoid prop drilling by using composition or context

## Authentication

- We are using SSR for authentication, NOT auth helpers
- Implement proper role-based access control
- Handle authentication state appropriately
- Protect routes that require authentication

## Data Flow

- Use server components for initial data fetching
- Use SWR or React Query for client-side data fetching and mutations
- Implement proper error handling for all data operations
- Use TypeScript types for all data structures

## Performance

- Optimize component rendering
- Implement proper code splitting
- Use Next.js Image component for images
- Implement proper caching strategies
- Monitor performance with Vercel Analytics

## Security

- Validate all user inputs
- Implement proper CSRF protection
- Use HTTPS for all API calls
- Follow security best practices for authentication
- Implement proper error handling

## Accessibility

- Follow WCAG guidelines
- Use semantic HTML
- Implement proper ARIA attributes
- Ensure keyboard navigation
- Test with screen readers

## Deployment

- Use Vercel for deployment
- Set up proper environment variables
- Implement proper CI/CD pipeline
- Use preview deployments for pull requests
- Monitor application health with Vercel Analytics

